0and%20up).%20With%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fsolo-401k%5C%22%3Esolo%20401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20type%20of%20retirement%20account%20designed%20for%20self-employed%20folks%20with%20no%20employees%20other%20than%20themselves%2C%20I%20can%20contribute%20both%20as%20an%20employer%20and%20as%20my%20own%20employee.%20On%20the%20employee%20side%2C%20I%20can%20stash%20away%20up%20to%20%2422%2C500%20in%202023.%20It's%2025%25%20of%20my%20net%20self-employment%20income%20on%20the%20employer%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20set%20up%20auto%20contributions%20to%20my%20HSA%20and%20IRA%20so%20that%20I%20can%20hit%20the%20maximum%20limits%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20As%20for%20my%20solo%20401(k)%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20perfect%20science%2C%20but%20I%20try%20to%20contribute%20funds%20as%20much%20as%20I%20can.%20I%20might%20squirrel%20away%20some%20money%20one%20month%20and%20nothing%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20planning%20a%20retirement%20where%20I'll%20be%20renting%20for%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20a%20chance%20that%20I%20might%20uproot%20and%20move%2C%20either%20because%20I%20want%20to%20go%20to%20a%20more%20affordable%20part%20of%20the%20US%20or%20because%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20I%20can%20more%20tangibly%20think%20about%20how%20much%20I%20would%20need%20in%20my%20retirement%20if%20I%20rented%20for%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20would%20be%20nice%20to%20own%20a%20home%20outright%20by%20the%20time%20I%20hit%20retirement%20age%2C%20currently%2C%20it's%20not%20feasible%20for%20me%20to%20own%20a%20single-family%20residence%20in%20my%20area.%20So%20I'm%20folding%20in%20housing%20expenses%20as%20part%20of%20my%20retirement%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20straddle%20two%20paths.%20It%20made%20me%20feel%20scattered.%20Now%20that%20I've%20nulled%20out%20savings%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20my%20financial%20go