h%20his%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8d69fc72ebc54a40e6fb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Larry%20Summers%3Cp%3ERobin%20Marchant%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Larry%20Summers%20says%20the%20Fed%20has%20redeemed%20itself.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV%20the%20central%20bank's%20post-COVID%20policy%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Begregious%26quot%3B%20mistake.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20Fed%20appears%20to%20have%20avoided%20his%20worst-case%20recession%20predictions%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20Summers%20considers%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20vindicated%20after%20its%20initial%20misstep%20on%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Treasury%20Secretary%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-08-23%2Fsummers-says-fed-recovered-from-egregious-inflation-mistake%3Fsrnd%3Dphx-economics-v2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20central%20bank's%20interest%20rate%20strategy%20has%20largely%20succeeded%2C%20even%20though%20Fed%20officials%20made%20a%20major%20blunder%20by%20first%20underestimating%20pandemic-era%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Fed%20mischaracterized%20inflation%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-used-car-prices-cpi-july-flatlined-transitory-price-growth-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btransitory%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20that%20COVID%20supply%20chain%20disruptions%20would%20eventually%20blow%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20climbed%20to%20more%20than%209%25%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20misjudgment%20was%20a%20pretty%20egregious%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Summers%20said%2C%20citing%20how%20the%20Fed%20expected%20for%20interest%20rates%20to%20remain%20at%20zero%20until%202024%3A%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20a%20low%20point%20in%20terms%20of%20monetary%20policy%20judgement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20central%20bankers%20grew%20to%20understand%20that%20inflation%20needed%20an%20interest%20rate%20response%2C%20the%20Fed%20initiated%20the%20most%20aggressive%20policy-tightening%20campaign%20in%20recent%20history.%20Since%20March%202022%2C%20the%20Fed%20funds%20rate%20has%20climbed%20from%20near-zero%20levels%20to%205.25%25-5.50%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20period%2C%20Summers%20often%20showcased%20skepticism%20that%20the%20Fed%20could%20clamp%20down%20on%20inflation%20this%20way%20without%20economic%20consequences.%20Though%20higher%20rates%20slow%20down%20price%20growth%2C%20they%20risk%20joblessness%20and%20an%20economic%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20August%202022%2C%20Summers%20was%20pricing%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-summers-predicts-likelihood-that-us-will-go-into-a-recession-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%25%20chance%20of%20a%20US%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20he%20also%20acknowledged%20smaller%20odds%20that%20inflation%20fades%20away%20without%20a%20meaningful%20deterioration%20in%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20his%20alternative%20forecast%20appears%20more%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20got%20to%20give%20it%20Fed%20credit%20for%20the%20fact%20that%2C%20while%20it%20wasn't%20always%20obvious%20that%20this%20would%20be%20the%20case%2C%20they%20moved%20strongly%20enough%20and%20vigorously%20enough%20to%20keep%20expectations%20anchored%2C%26quot%3B%20Summers%20told%20Bloomberg%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20recession%20looks%20increasingly%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20consequence%2C%20I%20think%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20growth%20statistics%20or%20the%20employment%20statistics%20through%20this%20period%2C%20they%20will%20be%20re