2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F1qcm5308_thapa_625x300_23_August_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20troops%20at%20Sirjap%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Major%20Dhan%20Singh%20Thapa%20was%20sent%20to%20Sirjap%20as%20commander%20of%20the%20Delta%20Company.%20All%20this%20time%2C%20the%20Chinese%20had%20been%20strengthening%20their%20posts%20and%20exerting%20psychological%20pressure%20on%20Indian%20troops%20through%20propaganda%20messages.%20What%20made%20things%20more%20challenging%20was%20that%20the%20Sirjap%20complex%2C%20maintained%20by%20assault%20boats%2C%20had%20no%20land%20connection%20to%20the%20Chushul%20Garrison.%20The%20Chinese%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20were%20well-prepared%2C%20and%20they%20were%20closing%20in.%20With%20direct%20road%20linkages%20to%20the%20place%20with%20Khurnak%20Fort%2C%20it%20was%20much%20easier%20for%20them%20to%20transport%20reinforcements%2C%20supplies%2C%20and%20heavy%20weaponry.%20Indian%20forces%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20had%20only%20personal%20weapons%20and%20LMGs%2C%20with%20the%20lake%20serving%20as%20the%20only%20supply%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Battle%20of%20Sirjap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indo-China%20war%20started%20on%20October%2020%2C%20and%20by%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20position%20at%20Sirjap-I%20had%20come%20under%20attack%20from%20Chinese%20artillery%20and%20mortars.%20The%20Gorkha%20troops%20at%20Sirjap-I%20had%20already%20been%20severely%20injured%20in%20the%20onslaught.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20the%20Chinese%20began%20to%20progressively%20approach%20the%20Indian%20stronghold%2C%20and%20Major%20Thapa's%20isolated%20company%20was%20assaulted%20heavily%20by%20the%20PLA%20forces.%20The%20Chinese%20soon%20came%20up%20with%20light%20tanks%2C%20against%20which%20Indian%20troops%20had%20no%20weapons.%20Even%20so%2C%20Major%20Thapa's%20Gorkha%20men%20managed%20to%20respond%20to%20three%20enemy%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20Thapa's%20company%20suffered%20greatly.%20When%20the%20Gorkhas'%20ammunition%20ran%20out%2C%20they%20took%20on%20the%20enemy%20with%20their%20'khukri'%2C%20yelling%20'%3Cem%3EJai%20Maa%20Kali%20Aayo%20Gorkhali%3C%2Fem%3E'.%20Just%20seven%20of%20Thapa's%2028%20troops%20survived%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%20battle.%20Sirjap-I%20fell%20to%20the%20enemy%20ultimately%2C%20and%20after%20overpowering%20the%20Indian%20forces%2C%20the%20Chinese%20captured%20Major%20Thapa%20as%20a%20prisoner%20of%20war.%20After%20heavy%20fighting%2C%20the%20Chinese%20also%20took%20control%20of%20Sirjap-II.%20Nobody%20survived%20there%20except%20Rifleman%20Tulsiram%20Thapa%2C%20who%20was%20captured%20by%20the%20Chinese%20but%20would%20later%20manage%20to%20sneak%20out%20in%20the%20dark.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Major%20General%20D.S.%20Thapa%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Thapa%20receiving%20the%20Param%20Vir%20Chakra%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Major%20General%20D.S.%20Thapa%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Thapa%20receiving%20the%20Param%20Vir%20Chakra%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F20tpc45o_thapa-2_625x300_23_August_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajor%20General%20D.S.%20Thapa%2C%20and%20right%2C%20Thapa%20receiving%20the%20Param%20Vir%20Chakra%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20All%20Were%20Assumed%20Dead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20from%20the%20observation%20post%20at%20Tokung%2C%20one%20could%20see%20smoke%20clouds%20rising%20over%20the%20embattled%20area.%20A%20patrol%20boat%20was%20dispatched%20from%20the%20battalion%20headquarters%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20led%20by%20Naik%20Rabi%20Lal%20Thapa.%20But%20barely%201%2C000%20yards%20from%20the%20post%2C%20the%20boat%20came%20under%20enemy%20attack%20and%20was%20forced%20to%20turn%20back%2C%20assuming%20that%20the%20entire%20Sirjap%20post%20had%20collapsed%20and%20that%20Major%20Thapa%20and%20his%20men%20had%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20when%20the%20headquarters%20decided%20to%20evacuate%20all%20the%20posts%20in%20Pangong%20Tso%2C%20including%20Yula%2C%20Naik%20Rabi%20Lal%20Thapa%20again%20volunteered%20to%20lead%20the%20effort.%20He%20eventually%20managed%20to%20evacuate%20all%20the%20casualties%20and%20the%20survivors%2C%20including%20the%20seven%20from%20the%20Thapa%20company%20and%20others%20from%20Yula-III.%20As%20for%20Yula-I%20and%20Yula-II%2C%20the%20Chinese%20surrounded%20both%20and%20cut%20off%20all%20escape%20routes%20for%20the%20posts.%20The%20Indians%20fought%20till%20the%20ammo%20ran%20out%2C%20but%20when%20communication%20died%2C%20all%20the%20men%20there%20were%20assumed%20to%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20soldiers%20fought%20till%20the%20last%20bullet.%20The%20seven%20men%20from%20the%20Thapa%20company%20who%20managed%20to%20be%20rescued%20in%20the%20dark%20of%20the%20night%20by%20boats%20later%20recounted%20how%20the%20enemy%20had%20lined%20up%20and%20shot%20dead%20all%20the%20severely%20wounded%20personnel%20who%20couldn't%20walk.%20In%20total%2C%20the%20Gorkhas%20lost%2033%20men%20at%20the%20battles%20of%20Sirjap%20and%20Yula.%20Rifleman%20Tulsiram%20Thapa%20received%20the%20Vir%20Chakra%2C%20Naik%20Rabi%20Lal%20Thapa%20was%20awarded%20the%20Mahavir%20Chakra%2C%20and%20Major%20Dhan%20Singh%20Thapa%20got%20the%20Paramvir%20Chakra%20(initially%20posthumously).%20In%201963%2C%20all%20the%20men%20taken%20as%20PoWs%2C%20including%20Major%20Dhan%20Singh%20Thapa%2C%20were%20repatriated%20to%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(All%20photos%20courtesy%20of%20the%20author)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Jai%20Samota%20is%20a%20student%20and%20writer%20from%20Barisadri%2C%20Chittorgarh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20author%20of%20'Major%20Shaitan%20Singh%2C%20PVC%3A%20The%20Man%20in%20Half%20Light')%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opini